headline.print_headline: Butler's Free Throws Lift Bulls Over Wolves
headline.main: Butler's Free Throws Lift Bulls Over Wolves

lead_paragraph: Jimmy Butler made a surprise return to the starting lineup and hit two free throws with 0.2 seconds left to help the Chicago Bulls weather another absence from star guard Derrick Rose in a 106-105 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Saturday night.
